Package: RNAPeaks
Type: Package
Title: RNA-Binding Protein Peak Visualization and Analysis  
Version: 1.2.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Krushna", "Bhanushali",
           email = "Krushna.Bhanushali@unc.edu",
           role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("Gilbert", "Giri",
           email = "Ggiri@unc.edu",
           role = c("aut")))
Description: RNAPeaks creates publicaition quality visualizations of RNA-binding
    protein (RBP) peaks overlaid on gene structures. Key features include                                                                                                                                 
      single-gene visualization with PlotGene(), multi-gene genomic region                                                                                                                                    
      plots with PlotRegion(), splicing maps analyzing RBP binding frequency                                                                                                                                  
      around splice junctions, and sequence motif frequency analysis with                                                                                                                                     
      IUPAC ambiguity code support.The package provides an interactive Shiny web interface                                                                                                                                    
      for users without R programming experience. Includes sample datasets                                                                                                                                    
      for immediate exploration.    
